*Background of Request*

Team Calendar use the default "Participation Role" which is "Req-Participant" as describe [here|http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2445.txt].

{code}ATTENDEE;X-CONFLUENCE-USER=phl;CN=Septa Cahyadiputra;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL:ma
 ilto:scahyadiputra@atlassian.com{code}

It would be great if we could change the attendee type to chair to avoid such issue. It is not a good practice to allow local calendar app to send invitations to all attendee when TeamCalendar ICS file imported into it as it will create unnecessary notification.

*Workaround*

# Open your exported {{ics}} file to your favourite text editor
# Search and replace the following string
{code}ATTENDEE;{code}
to
{code}ATTENDEE;ROLE=CHAIR:{code}
# Save As to save it using a different filename to ensure the original is kept intact for safety purposes

